        {
          "id": "x-adityaag-2026-05-01-p2-s2",
          "text": "Cybersecurity has a new shape: AI is both the threat and the only viable solution. @nikesharora, CEO of @PaloAltoNtwks, joined me at @southpkcommons to break down what’s next. (00:30) Big problems vs. fast wins (04:00) Joining Google (07:00) Larry Page's product obsession (10:00) He read every hiring packet himself (13:00) What Silicon Valley gets wrong about Masa Son (16:00) Successful founders never wish they took less risk (17:00) Joining Palo Alto knowing nothing about cybersecurity (20:00) What incumbents got wrong when ChatGPT launched (23:00) Security was never built into AI (28:00) No enterprise knows what's running inside its stack (31:00) AI finds bad code faster than humans ever could (35:00) The only way to fix the chaos is more AI (38:00) AI won't just automate work—it raises the floor (41:00) Foundation models vs. specialized stacks (45:00) Why communication is 30% of the job at scale",
